<%@ Page Title="About" Language="C#" MasterPageFile="~/Site.Master" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeBehind="About.aspx.cs" Inherits="All_Liberia.About" %>

<asp:Content ID="BodyContent" ContentPlaceHolderID="MainContent" runat="server">

    <style type="text/css">
        .para {
            font-family: Calibri;
            font-size: medium;
        }
        
    </style>
    <div class="jumbotron" style="background-color:#AF353A;">
        <div id="aboutContainer" style="background-color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 5px;">
            <fieldset>
                <legend><%:Title %> All-liberia.com</legend>

                <br />
                <p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium;">
                   ll-Liberia.com is a web portal created by Liberian technocrats, visionaries and patriots, as a one-stop shop for everything that involves Liberia, and to exhibits the true beauty of the country as well as expose to visitors the world’s hidden treasure – the nation of Liberia.
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium;">
                    The information on this site has come not from one source, but a whole cluster of resources from well-respected and reliable organizations like encyclopedia, Wikipedia, the CIA fact book, travel entities, BBC World Service, Africa.com, allafrica.com, etc., to quickly help you get and stay ahead. Instead of surfing from one website to the next to acquire the rightful information about Liberia, we have gone ahead and done the do-diligence and all of the ground works for you and compiled them onto a single portal.
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium;">
                    Whether you are a nationalist looking for a way to contribute to the country, a student, doing a research, a tourist looking for the right travel information, an investor anticipating on investing in the country, a detractor or just being noisy, this site is the perfect place to come. 
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium;">
                    All-Liberia.com strives to fulfill the following objectives: 
                </p>
                <ul class="para">
                    <li>Showcase Liberia on the world stage—its beauty, its hospitality, its rich cultures and natural resources and its potential
                    </li>
                    <li>Promote meaningful, civilized and strategic dialogues and discussions on how to move the country forward 
                    </li>
                    <li>Expose Liberians to the wealth of resources available to them through the world wide web so as to facilitate learning endeavors
                    </li>
                    <li>Serve as an interactive learning resource for Liberian students researchers   </li>
                    <li>Help Liberians understand the country’s past odyssey in order to make sound decisions about the future.
                    </li>
                    <li>Connect tourists/travelers to the appropriate resources that facilitate their journey to Liberia

                    </li>
                    <li>Expose Liberians to the enormous reservoirs of entertainment from their own talented artists. 
                    </li>
                    <li>Link visitors to the literature and literary works by some of Liberia’s best thinkers, writers and historians like Joseph Saye Guanue, Wilton Sankawolo, etc. 

                    </li>
                    <li>Keep visitors updated and informed about the happenings in and around Liberia, through various news media and news feeds from well renowned resources.

                    </li>
                    <li>Help Liberians air their views on sensitive topics such as corruption, governance, development, war, education, poverty, tribalism, etc. 
                    </li>

                </ul>
                <p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium;">
                    Thanks for visiting. We encourage you to come often as the discussion and information on this site is updated consistently to keep you abreast on current events. 
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium;">
                    Your suggestions and constructive criticisms are highly encouraged and appreciated to help improve the site. Please email us or send your comments at our comment page or give use a buzz at 123-098-1234. 
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium;">
                    Again, thanks for stopping by. 
                </p>
            </fieldset>
        </div>
    </div>
